<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-06-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-06-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="175" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d175">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">894.24/1545</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">British Embassy</gloss> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                            </hi><note n="25" xml:id="d175fn1">Transmitted to the Department on June
                                9.</note>
                        </head>
                        <dateline>
                            <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian" when="1941-06-03">June 3, 1941</date>
                        </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Telegram From London Dated June</hi> 3<hi rend="smallcaps">rd</hi> 1941</p>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="italic">Japan</hi>. His Majesty’s Ambassador at Tokyo has been
                            instructed to make it clear to the Japanese Minister for Foreign Affairs
                            that we are not prepared to exert influence on the Netherlands
                            Government to increase the supply of rubber from Netherlands East Indies
                            to Japan particularly as we are not satisfied that Japan is not
                            facilitating the acquisition by Germany of the rubber from Indo-China
                            and elsewhere.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>